						<summary>

						<p>Fragment of a slab set up near the Bijjappa-Nāyaḍu's hall.</p>						

						<p>Circa 9th century.</p>						

						<p>It seems to register some gift of land and garden and refers to <hi rend="italic">puṇṇame.</hi> Details are all lost.</p>						

